Jasco and Royal Bafokeng: South African Stock Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-08T06:23:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/jasco-old-mutual-royal-bafokeng-south-african-stock-preview.html
(Corrects year earlier earnings in Compu-Clearing.)  The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index declined for a second
day, falling 38.85, or 0.1 percent, to 32,298.21 at the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg.    Compu-Clearing Outsourcing Ltd. (CCL)  : The freight
forwarding and clearing company said first-half earnings rose to
3.7 million rand ($537,837) in the period through December, from
3.2 million rand a year earlier. The share closed unchanged at
2.40 rand.  Jasco Electronic Holdings Ltd. (JSC SJ): The South African
telecommunications company said earnings per share in the first-
half through December will probably be between 65 percent and 75
percent lower than the 10 cents it reported in the year earlier,
according to a trading statement released to the stock exchange
yesterday. Jasco closed unchanged at 1.24 rand.    Old Mutual Plc (OML)  : the U.K.â€™s third-biggest insurer
publishes annual earnings for the year through December. The
stock declined 9 cents, or 0.6 percent, to 15.02 rand.    Royal Bafokeng Platinum Ltd. (RBP)  : The platinum-mining
company publishes results for the year through December. The
company said on Feb. 4 that per-share earnings would be between
21.97 rand and 22.68 rand. The stock climbed 50 cents, or 0.8
percent, to 63.85 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
